  "imageCount": 4,
  "body": "<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/baf5154ebe92cfaf.jpg?v=1782531579\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n<p>I tend to get obsessed with things. Right now I am pretty obsessed with the sweater from <a href=\"http://www.shareasale.com/r.cfm?B=286192&amp;U=530666&amp;M=31374&amp;urllink=\">Cents of Style</a>. I'll be wearing it at least once a week, so if you see me in real life in the next month, there's a good chance this is what I will be wearing. Plus it's for the <a href=\"http://www.shareasale.com/r.cfm?B=286192&amp;U=530666&amp;M=31374&amp;urllink=\">Give More Good campaign</a>, so you can feel extra good about your purchase going to help women in need.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/c7b8fde2df3f23c3.jpg?v=1782531582\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>You probably already know how obsessed I am with <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/caseyneistat\">Casey Neistat's videos</a>. Here's <a href=\"https://youtu.be/M7bujTQwZ1Q\">the video of the fangirl tee</a> I made. He showed me in it in <a href=\"https://youtu.be/RygLVGaabf4\">his Vidcon vlog</a> (around 2:55). Well he decided to <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l-yrXB95qDo\">end his daily vlog</a> (I fell behind when he took a little break, so I have a few more episodes to look forward to). His vlog was what got me obsessed with making more videos and drones. Usually I have the ability to justify big purchases, but I could not figure out how I could make the investment into a drone if I had no idea what I was going to do with it. Luckily, it was happy holladays to me as Yuneec reached out to see if I wanted to try the Breeze. I'm still playing with it. My first impressions are that it is a great device for the price point. The controller is my iPhone and the app is easy to use. Though I am a bit nervous about flying it and crashing it (I've watched too many Casey Neistat videos), I think the Breeze is great little addition to my devices. It's lightweight and compact. I even took it to Japan and will be including some of the footage in an upcoming video. Considering I still haven't completely unpacked from that trip, it may be a few weeks before you see it. Ann-Marie captured this shot:</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/eaca4df9ad88a227.jpg?v=1782531584\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>And here is the straight out of the camera of the drone shot around the same moment:</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/57b73f054758d472.jpg?v=1782531587\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Excited to try it out more - if you have any tips or ideas of what kind of shots you want to see, let me know. If you want to add it along with the sweater to your wishlist, I think you may become obsessed with it too. Also I have some really fun announcements coming up in the next couple weeks - happy holla days!</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
}